Sentencas: The poor structural stability and high thermal expansion coefficient of YBaCo2O5+delta (YBCO) cathode seriously impede its practical application in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: YBaCo2O5+δ-based double-perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with simultaneously improved structural stability and thermal expansion properties

Sentencas: Herein, single- and double-doped YBaCoCuO5+delta (YBCC), YBaCoFeO5+delta (YBCF) and YBaCo2/3Fe2/3Cu2/3O5+delta (YBCFC) are comparatively studied to assess the influences of doping strategy on stability, thermal and chemical compatibilities.
Titulo: YBaCo2O5+δ-based double-perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with simultaneously improved structural stability and thermal expansion properties

Sentencas: The improvement of structural stability and thermal expansion properties of YBCO is achieved simultaneously by the Fe or/and Cu doping in Co-site.
Titulo: YBaCo2O5+δ-based double-perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with simultaneously improved structural stability and thermal expansion properties

Sentencas: First-principles calculations further confirm that the substitution of Fe or/and Cu for Co improve the structural stability compared to undoped YBCO.
Titulo: YBaCo2O5+δ-based double-perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with simultaneously improved structural stability and thermal expansion properties

Sentencas: The YBCC and YBCFC exhibit good thermal and chemical compatibility with La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) electrolyte below 950 degrees C. Moreover, the YBCC cathode displays better electro-catalytic activity in the studied cathodes, in which the area specific resistance is 0.138 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: YBaCo2O5+δ-based double-perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with simultaneously improved structural stability and thermal expansion properties

Sentencas: The YBCC cathode shows good electrochemical stability over a 20-h test period.
Titulo: YBaCo2O5+δ-based double-perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with simultaneously improved structural stability and thermal expansion properties

Sentencas: The Cu-doped YBCC double perovskite has stable structure and excellent thermal and chemical compatibility, making it a good cathode candidate for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: YBaCo2O5+δ-based double-perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with simultaneously improved structural stability and thermal expansion properties

Sentencas: Our findings provide a promising strategy to simultaneously improve structural stability and thermal expansion properties in Co-based perovskites, thus greatly extending their applications.
Titulo: YBaCo2O5+δ-based double-perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with simultaneously improved structural stability and thermal expansion properties
